The paper discusses the detection of malicious domains using DNS data analysis, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for data analysis, which could fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of data enrichment techniques, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the challenges of processing large amounts of data, which could fall under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
